    "updated_at": "2013-11-01T19:49:25Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The addition to the config file doc really points to the fact that our config file docs should not be anything like what they are. Telling users how to configure IPython and detailing the inner workings of the config system shouldn't happen in the same place.\n\nWe need a separate 'this is how you configure IPython' doc, and that shouldn't need to even mention that JSON config files exist. At that level, only _APIs_ for persisting config should be described.\n"
  },
